ocument. It instead cuts off the available text at any time, e.g. at the previous or next paragraph. This makes it hard to provide AI-based features that require more context.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"KeyboardKit Pro therefore unlocks ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/UIKit\/UITextDocumentProxy\/fullDocumentContext(config:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" proxy extensions that let you read ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"all"}]},{"text":" text from the proxy:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let proxy = keyboardContext.textDocumentProxy","let result = try await proxy.fullDocumentContext()"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This will provide you with all the text before and after the input cursor, as well as an aggregate of all the available text in the document.","type":"text"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The full document read operation is a best effort operation, that makes the most of the very limited capabilities that are provided by the operating system. It’s not guaranteed to return a valid result. You can configure the operation to yield better results, for instance by waiting longer when moving the input cursor, try to move more times around the edges, etc."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note"}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/keyboardkitpro\/proxy-article"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]},{"paths":["\/documentation\/keyboardkitpro\/proxy-article"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"This article describes the KeyboardKit proxy engine and its utilities.","type":"text"}],"references":{"doc://com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro/documentation/KeyboardKitPro/UIKit/UITextDocumentProxy/hasUnclosedQuotationBeforeInput(for:)":{"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind"